---
import MelvinLayout from '../../../layouts/MelvinLayout.astro';
---

<MelvinLayout 
    title="The Library"
    description="Melvin Lim's Reading List (Sandel, LKY) and Selected Essays on Diplomacy, Meritocracy, and Legal Theory."
>
    <section class="page-header container">
        <span class="eyebrow">Input / Output</span>
        <h1>The Library</h1>
        <p class="lead">Ideas I am consuming, and ideas I am producing.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="container layout-grid">
        
        <!-- Left: Reading List (Input) -->
        <aside class="reading-section">
            <h2 class="section-label">Currently Reading</h2>
            
            <div class="book-item">
                <span class="book-status">Active</span>
                <img src="/assets/images/projects/melvin/book-justice.webp" alt="Justice Book Cover" class="book-cover" />
                <h3>Justice: What's the Right Thing to Do?</h3>
                <p class="book-author">Michael Sandel</p>
                <div class="book-meta">Exploring utilitarianism vs. libertarianism.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="book-item dim">
                <span class="book-status">Queue</span>
                <img src="/assets/images/projects/melvin/book-hard-truths.webp" alt="Hard Truths Book Cover" class="book-cover" />
                <h3>Hard Truths</h3>
                <p class="book-author">Lee Kuan Yew</p>
            </div>

            <div class="book-item dim">
                <span class="book-status">Queue</span>
                <h3>The Brothers Karamazov</h3>
                <p class="book-author">Fyodor Dostoevsky</p>
            </div>
        </aside>

        <!-- Right: Essays (Output) -->
        <main class="essays-section">
            <h2 class="section-label">Selected Writing</h2>

            <article class="essay-item">
                <span class="essay-date">2024 • Saints MUN • Deputy Chair</span>
                <h3>Diplomacy in a Fragile World</h3>
                <p class="essay-abstract">
                    Reflections on <strong>Prof. Kishore Mahbubani's</strong> address. He spoke on the paradox of global interdependence vs. geopolitical fragility. The key takeaway: ASEAN acts as a critical shield against Great Power rivalry. Diplomacy isn't just about principles; it's about holding space for dialogue when tensions rise.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="essay-item">
                <span class="essay-date">2024 • Dialogue with Minister Chan Chun Sing</span>
                <h3>The Trade-offs of Meritocracy</h3>
                <p class="essay-abstract">
                    A candid discussion on the "imperfect but necessary" nature of meritocracy. Minister Chan emphasized <em>Ikigai</em>—aligning passion, mission, vocation, and profession. My reflection: Efficiency matters, but a compassionate society requires us to value diverse talents beyond the academic scorecard.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="essay-item">
                <span class="essay-date">2023 • 13th S Rajaratnam Lecture</span>
                <h3>Resilience as Foreign Policy</h3>
                <p class="essay-abstract">
                    President Halimah Yacob's insight: "Many countries would mourn our absence." This struck a chord. As a small nation, our relevance relies on our internal cohesion. Domestic unity is the currency we trade with on the global stage.
                </p>
            </article>

            <a href="#" class="essay-item">
            <span class="essay-date">Finalist</span>
            <h3>NUS Sejarah Inquisition</h3>
            <p>"Reimagining the Sang Nila Utama Narrative." A critique of colonial historiography.</p>
        </a>

            <article class="essay-item">
                <span class="essay-date">2024 • NUS Sejarah Inquisition • Top 3 Finalist</span>
                <h3>Preserving Culinary Heritage</h3>
                <p class="essay-abstract">
                    An exploration of Singapore's "Dying Traditions" through the lens of traditional pastries. Globalization isn't just an economic threat; it's a cultural one. Preserving identity requires active stewardship of our vanishing food culture.
                </p>
            </article>

        </main>
    </div>

</MelvinLayout>

<style>
    .page-header {
        padding-top: 8rem;
        padding-bottom: 4rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
    }

    .eyebrow {
        font-family: var(--mv-font-sans);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.15em;
        color: var(--mv-accent);
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        display: block;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: 3.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .lead {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        color: var(--mv-text-muted);
    }

    .layout-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr;
        gap: 4rem;
        padding: 4rem 0 8rem 0;
    }

    .section-label {
        font-family: var(--mv-font-sans);
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        color: var(--mv-text-muted);
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        display: block;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
        padding-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    /* Books */
    .book-item {
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }

    .book-item.dim { opacity: 0.5; }

    .book-status {
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
        padding: 2px 6px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        display: inline-block;
    }

    .book-item h3 {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        margin: 0.5rem 0 0.2rem 0;
    }

    .book-author {
        font-family: var(--mv-font-serif);
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--mv-text-muted);
        margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    }

    .book-meta {
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        color: var(--mv-text-muted);
        line-height: 1.4;
    }

    .book-cover {
        width: 60px;
        height: 90px;
        float: left; 
        margin-right: 1rem; 
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        object-fit: cover;
        border-radius: 4px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
    }

    /* Essays */
    .essay-item {
        margin-bottom: 4rem;
        display: block;
        text-decoration: none; /* Remove default underline */
        color: inherit; /* Inherit white color */
        transition: opacity 0.2s;
    }

    .essay-item:hover {
        opacity: 0.8;
    }

    .essay-date {
        font-family: var(--mv-font-mono);
        color: var(--mv-accent);
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        display: block;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .essay-item h3 {
        font-size: 1.75rem;
        margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    }

    .essay-abstract {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        color: var(--mv-text-muted);
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        max-width: 600px;
    }

    .read-link {
        color: var(--mv-text-main);
        text-decoration: none;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--mv-accent);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .layout-grid {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            gap: 4rem;
        }
    }
</style>
